title: For Sale:  Rare Limited Scar 17
location: Smithfield, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: This is a New In Box Limited Initial Production run Scar 17s. The first ones were made here in the US at the same plant that made the ones for the military. After the initial run they moved production to Belgium. They came in a Storm case with 2 mags and a Certificate of Authenticity. You dont find these everyday and are very rare.  This is gun 186 of less than 1000 in the world to exist and less than half are Flat Dark Earth. The Limited 17s had 3 digit serial number where the Limited 16s had 7 digit serial number. No record of how many were actually produced and sold. Only the factory round has been fired at the factory and has remained unfired since. If you know Browning/FN guns then you know what you are looking at. I already sold one with a higher serial number. If there are no good offers then i will sell this one to the same person. Thought i would give someone else the chance to buy or trade for this beauty. In this package the light comes with the standard pressure switch, the Click On/Off Tail Cap, the Rear Cap for the pressure switch and all mounts to any rail. The Light was purchased only a week ago and is now back in the orginal box. I say all that to prove the light is in Excellent condition. The Thorntail Offset Light Mount retails at about $50 (you can Youtube it and confirm it's quality) and is an excellent Picatinny rail mount that has been made specifically for the Surefire M-Series Tactical Lights, made by a high quality brand and company, Haley Strategic.  I'm only interested in serious buyers. No trades, no shipping deliveries. Only cash.
